The paper deals with wireless sensor networks, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The optimization problem formulated in the paper involves power allocation and subchannel assignment, which are common topics in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of the Lyapunov drift-plus-penalty method suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.MA) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents numerical results to evaluate the proposed algorithm, which is a common practice in the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
